{"rawJson":null,"m_plot":"A young couple loses control of their motorbike while riding in a forest. Jim is badly hurt, so Lori runs to find some help. Only finding an abandoned cabin, she runs back to Jim only to find him dead hanging upside down from a tree. Terrified, she tries to run back to the cabin but is killed she steps on a trap full of sharp objects. | Weeks later, a group of campers, Dennis, Margaret, Wendy, Marco, Nathaniel, Boone, Eggar, Vanessa, Mike and Melanie, arrive at the forest. The group makes a clearing and spend the night around a bonfire. When they wake the next morning, Marco and Eggar are missing. While the others search for them, Mike takes a swim with Melanie following. They have sex during which Mike is stabbed by a strange creature. Melanie screams in terror as she watches him die. | Nathaniel and Dennis find the abandoned cabin and an old grave. Dennis enters the cabin and Nathaniel hears him scream. He rushes in and is attacked by a strange old lady who turns out to be Dennis trying to scare him. They search the cabin, scavenging food and items to take and find the severed head of a wolf in a cabinet. Shaken, they head back to the camp. | That night, the strange creature attacks Margaret in her sleep. She hysterically tells the others what she saw. The campers hear a strange noise and pursue the source only to find Marco, who has returned to camp. Vanessa gets angry at the guys for scaring the girls and walks off alone. When she enters the old outhouse, Mike's severed head falls on her and she screams. Nathaniel and the rest of the group come to her aid, then begin to search for Melanie who they assumed was still with Mike. Unsuccessful, they decide to spend one more night in the camp. In the morning, they go to the cabin to try to find Mike's killer who, unbeknownst to the group, is down in the basement with Melanie. They find a human hand in a jar and flee. They raft along the river, unaware that the creature is following them. The 